OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782233278
OL,3,CHow to beat the heat as UK faces
OL,4,C'tropical nights'
OL,6,FForecasters say overnight heat could
OL,7,Fbe more sustained in some places in
OL,8,Fthe coming days, reaching "tropical
OL,9,Fnight conditions", where temperatures
OL,10,Fnever fall below 20C.
OL,12,FTropical nights are still "relatively
OL,13,Finfrequent", the Met Office told ITV
OL,14,FNews, but the forecaster said these
OL,15,Fconditions would likely be met across
OL,16,Fparts of England and Wales, especially
OL,17,Fin urban areas. Humidity is also a
OL,18,Ffactor, often making the hot weather
OL,19,Ffeel even more challenging.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
