OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782233278
OL,3,CHow to beat the heat as UK faces
OL,4,C'tropical nights'
OL,6,FWith only a fifth of UK homes equipped
OL,7,Fwith air conditioning, hot nighttime
OL,8,Ftemperatures can lead to poor sleep.
OL,9,FIf your body's core temperature
OL,10,Fincreases, it can disrupt your ability
OL,11,Fto fall and stay asleep.
OL,13,FThis can be a lose-lose situation, as
OL,14,Fgood quality sleep is essential to
OL,15,Fhelp regulate body temperature.
OL,17,FHere are some tips and tricks to help
OL,18,Fyou stay cool overnight.
OL,20,FDitch the alcohol and caffeine
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782233278
OL,3,CHow to beat the heat as UK faces
OL,4,C'tropical nights'
OL,6,FAlcohol tends to worsen sleep quality,
OL,7,Fespecially if consumed just before bed.
OL,9,FIt also acts as a diuretic which means
OL,10,Fyour body is encouraged to lose fluid,
OL,11,Frisking dehydration and increasing
OL,12,Fyour body temperature.
OL,14,FThe body usually winds down to sleep
OL,15,Fby cooling its internal core
OL,16,Ftemperature. If this remains high, it
OL,17,Fcan make it harder to drift off.
OL,19,FCaffeine is also a diuretic, so swap
OL,20,Fto a caffeine free alternative and you
OL,21,Fmay feel a little bit cooler.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782233278
OL,3,CHow to beat the heat as UK faces
OL,4,C'tropical nights'
OL,6,FChange where you sleep
OL,8,FHot air rises, so if you can, consider
OL,9,Fmoving downstairs for a night or two
OL,10,Ffor a more comfortable sleep.
OL,12,FIf your home is on one level, move to
OL,13,Fthe coolest area to try and give
OL,14,Fyourself as much respite as possible.
OL,16,FFreezers aren't just for food
OL,18,FIf you need an instant cooling effect,
OL,19,Ftry throwing your bedding and pyjamas
OL,20,Finto the freezer ahead of bed time.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782233278
OL,3,CHow to beat the heat as UK faces
OL,4,C'tropical nights'
OL,6,FWhile they won't remain cool the whole
OL,7,Fnight, it could keep you cool enough
OL,8,Fto help you get to sleep.
OL,10,FIf you're looking for a longer cold
OL,11,Fhit, a hot water bottle filled with
OL,12,Fcold water can be put in the freezer
OL,13,Fas well.
OL,15,FTry freezing for only 20 minutes
OL,16,Fbefore bed, in order to avoid the
OL,17,Fpossibility of ice burn.
OL,19,FHave a cool shower before bed
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782233278
OL,3,CHow to beat the heat as UK faces
OL,4,C'tropical nights'
OL,6,FA refreshing cool or lukewarm shower
OL,7,Fcan help to lower your core body
OL,8,Ftemperature.
OL,10,FTurn off any unnecessary electrical
OL,11,Fitems
OL,13,FElectrical items give off heat, and
OL,14,Fcan do so even when in standby mode.
OL,16,FUnplug any of those non-essential
OL,17,Fdevices for the night such as TVs,
OL,18,Fchargers, laptops and computers.
OL,20,FTo pyjama or not to pyjama?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782233278
OL,3,CHow to beat the heat as UK faces
OL,4,C'tropical nights'
OL,6,FIf your room and bedding are cool,
OL,7,Fthen going to bed without pyjamas can
OL,8,Fhelp you maintain that lower
OL,9,Ftemperature.
OL,11,FHowever, if your room is hot, humid
OL,12,Fand stuffy then pyjamas can be
OL,13,Fpreferable - they can absorb sweat,
OL,14,Fallowing it to evaporate and cool you
OL,15,Fdown.
OL,17,FThe pyjamas have to be loose and
OL,18,Fbreathable though, as tight ones will
OL,19,Ftrap warm air close to the body.
OL,21,FHydration, hydration, hydration
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1782233278
OL,3,CHow to beat the heat as UK faces
OL,4,C'tropical nights'
OL,6,FBeing dehydrated, especially in the
OL,7,Fhot weather, can be incredibly
OL,8,Fdangerous.
OL,10,FIf you are so dehydrated that you
OL,11,Fcan't sweat, then you can't cool
OL,12,Fyourself effectively, meaning you'll
OL,13,Fhave a poor night's sleep.
OL,15,FDrink a glass of cold water before bed
OL,16,Fand keep one close during the night
OL,17,Ffor any top ups.
OL,19,FTry facing your fan outside your window
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
